source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1951, 1964, 1973, 1985, 1993, 2005, 2018 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) official estimates through 2023; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the 1990, 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS survey estimates have been considered.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2022; (b) birth-histories data from the 1986, 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010 DHS; (c) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 2005 Census; (d) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1985, 1993, 2005 censuses; (e) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1964, 1973, 2005, 2018 censuses. In addition, the (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2017; (b) birth-histories data from the 1976 WFS and 1990, 2015 DHS; (c) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 2018 Census; (d) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1973, 2018 censuses and 1976 WFS; (e) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1951, 1985, 1993 censuses and 1955-2011 Education Stats and 1978 ENH; (f) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1973, 1985, 1993, 2005, 2018 censuses and 1986, 1990, 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2010; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2021; (c) adjusted for underreporting of infant and child deaths; (d) adult deaths adjusted for underregistration using death distribution methods; (e) mortality rates for older ages were adjusted.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1950-2010 Estimates; (b) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (c) siblings deaths from the 2015 DHS; (d) maternal orphanhood from the 1978 ENH and 1985 Census and 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS; (e) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1973, 1985, 1993, 2005 censuses; (f) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1973, 1985, 1993, 2005 censuses; (g) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (h) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 2005 Census; (b) paternal orphanhood from the 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS; (c) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1978 ENH and 1986, 1990, 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS; (d) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1978 ENH and 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS; (e) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2017; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1976 WFS and 1986, 1990, 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015 DHS; (c) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1973, 1985, 1993 censuses and 1978 CPS and 1978, 1980 ENH; (d) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2023; (b) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 2005 Census; (c) recent household deaths from the 1950-2017 Estimates and 2005, 2018 censuses have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination (Latin American countries, Spain and United States of America); (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum. In addition, the estimates of migrant flows, and assumed subsequent trends in international migration have been considered.
